Biography

2023-24:

Appeared in 14 of NU’s 36 games

Netted the Huskies’ opening goal en route to a 5-3 victory over #1 Boston College (12/1)

Finished with six shots on goal and five blocked shots

Recorded a season-high two shots twice against #1 Boston College (12/1) and Brown (12/9)

2022-23:

Appeared in 27 of NU’s 35 games in his first season with the Huskies

Finished with eight points from one goal and seven assists

His eight points rank fifth among all Northeastern defensemen

Tallied his first goal in his first game as a Husky in an overtime win against LIU (10/1)

Recorded a season-high two points with two assists in a 6-2 win over New Hampshire (11/4)

Finished with a plus-eight rating and 18 blocks

Missed the final 11 games of the season due to injury

Before Northeastern: Played for the Penticton Vees (BCHL) during the 2021-22 season... Totaled three goals and 24 assists for 27 points in as many games played... Tallied seven playoff assists in 17 appearances... Played his freshmen season at Boston University in 2021, appearing in eight games for the Terriers, tallying an assist... Spent 2018-21 with the Dubuque Fighting Saints (USHL)... Totaled 104 appearances for the Saints, with 12 goals, 45 assists for 57 points and a plus-nine rating... Tallied a playoff goal for the Saints in 2020-21... Spent time with the Boston Jr. Bruins, the Boston Little Bruins, Lawrence Academy, and Shattuck St. Mary's 14U... Won the John Carlton Memorial Award from the Boston Bruins in 2019

Personal: Son of Tim and Jeanna... Has one sibling, Ava... Father Tim played college hockey at Merrimack College, went on to play in the ECHL... Majoring in Business Administration

NHL: Los Angeles Kings | 2019 | Round 6 | Pick 157
